               <interp inst="t17470116-41" type="collection" value="BAILEY"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470116-41" type="year" value="1747"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470116-41" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/17470116"></interp>
               <interp inst="t17470116-41" type="date" value="17470116"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t17470116-41-off170-c398" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470116-41-defend491 t17470116-41-off170 t17470116-41-verdict173"></join>
         
               <p>119. 
               
                  <persName id="t17470116-41-defend491" type="defendantName">
                     Charles 
                     Gerey 
                  <interp inst="t17470116-41-defend491" type="surname" value="Gerey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-defend491" type="given" value="Charles"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-defend491" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was <rs id="t17470116-41-off170" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-off170" type="offenceCategory" value="kill"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-off170" type="offenceSubcategory" value="murder"></interp>
               indicted for throwing 
                     <persName id="t17470116-41-victim492" type="victimName">
                        Dorothy 
                        Grisdell 
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-victim492" type="surname" value="Grisdell"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17470116-41-victim492" type="given" value="Dorothy"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17470116-41-victim492" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470116-41-off170 t17470116-41-victim492"></join>
                     </persName>
                    against a wooden Petition, and giving her on the Stomach and Side, several mortal Bruises ; of which Bruises she languished till she died
            </rs>, the <rs id="t17470116-41-cd171" type="crimeDate">17th of November</rs>
                  <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470116-41-off170 t17470116-41-cd171"></join>.</p>
               <p>The whole of this Affair appeared to be a drunken Quarrel between the deceased's Husband and the Prisoner, who <rs id="t17470116-41-deflabel172" type="occupation">keeps a Publick-house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17470116-41-defend491 t17470116-41-deflabel172"></join>: as the Prisoner was fighting with her Husband, she interfered, and got herself thrown against the Wainscott, which<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="174701160036"></xptr> might or might not be the Cause of her Death ; for by the Evidence, it appeared her Husband was a very sorry Fellow, and had used her, very ill, and made several Motions to strike her, before this Affair happened. The Prisoner was <rs id="t17470116-41-verdict173" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17470116-41-verdict173" type="verdictCategory" value="notGuilty"></interp>
               acquitted
            </rs>, but deservedly censured for keeping such a disorderly House.</p>
